flowRoot.flowPara: Feature selection is a method used in machine learning to find a small subset of features in order to build a more accurate, simpler and faster model. It is often used with high dimensional data.

Interpretation of those features can be costly in some domain (e.g. biomedical application), hence domain experts would prefer more robust feature selection methods to have more confidence in the selected features.
One approach for more robust results are ensemble methods
In ensemble learning multiple algorithms are combined to obtain better performance or stability.
Symmetrical Uncertainty Measures the normalized mutual information between single features (F) and their class (C).
RELIEF Samples are taken randomly and compared in terms of similarity to their nearest neighboring sample.
SVM RFE Recursive feature elimination fits a support vector machine (SVM) and ranks the feature actcording to their according to their importance in the model.
Ensemble methods The weights of different feature selection methods are first computed and then linearly aggregated to obtain the new weights.
Lasso A penalized version of logistic regression was used. The weight vector is used for weighting the features.
An advantage of a Lasso model is that the weight vector is extremely sparse due to the L1 Norm.
We build on the work of Saeys et al. (2008) by combining multiple feature selection methods with different ensemble methods.
Averaging The mean of the weights is used as the new weight.
Yvan Saeys, Thomas Abeel, and Yves Van de Peer. Robust Feature Selection Using En-
semble Feature Selection Techniques, pages 313–325. Springer Berlin Heidelberg, Berlin,
Graphics: Yang, Pengyi, et al. "A review of ensemble methods in bioinformatics." Current Bioinformatics 5.4 (2010): 296-308.
The set of features chosen by feature selector :
Jaccard index was used to measure the similarity between two feature selectons.
10 random subsets of data were taken.
Each subset was weighted with the feature selection methods.
The similarity between the subsets was calculated with Jaccard index for the 1% best features.

The averaging ensemble method is always one of the best, if not the best, in terms of performance. However, while the stability of the selected features was higher than the Lasso and the SVM RFE, it was often considerably lower with RELIEF and SU. On some data sets (e. g. GISETTE) SU was the best trade-off between stability and performance. Moreover weighting the feature selectors according to their performance did not change the result considerably. It was at best as good as the mean, and sometimes even worse.
Ensemble Methods for Robust Feature Selection
accuracy is estimated for each of the feature selectors for multiple classifiers. The feature selectors are then weighted according to their performance.
